{% block main_content %}


<p>A placement is a work experience that forms part of a
degree, where you will often undertake an assignment, progress reports or other
learning activities in addition to the tasks you perform within the role you
have undertaken.<p>

</p>
<ul>
 <li>Takes various forms but is part of
     your degree, usually your 3<sup>rd</sup> year (undergraduate)</li>
 <li>Involves
     graduate level recruitment processes and employment status</li>
 <li>Often lasts 12 months but can be much shorter (a month, 3 months or 6 months)</li>
 <li>Frequently paid
     – on average £15,000 to £17,000 per annum</li>
 <li>Helps develop
     commercial awareness, sector specific knowledge and wide range of
     employability skills</li>
 <li>Find out more from your academic department; as a placement is part of your degree, your department will be able to provide you with the relevant information and support.</li>
</ul>




